  "text": "In 1999 Alvarez et al. proposed the analog version of the LMS spectrum analyzer, where the coefficients are adapted independently by analog LMS structure which can be implemented in the VLSI technology. The main advantage gained from the work is that since the adaptation is carried out in the continuous time domain, real time computing speed was achieved [CITATION_1] .",
